lias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/08\/16\/prophet-walks-sahabah-ride\/","url_meta":{"origin":19386,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Humility: The Prophet walks, his companions ride","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 16, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud reported: On the day of Badr, we were riding with three men upon one camel. Abu Lubabah and Ali ibn Abi Talib were the two riding with the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him. It was time for the Messenger of Allah to walk,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":11519,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/01\/18\/do-not-curse-insult-sahabah\/","url_meta":{"origin":19386,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Sahaba: Do not curse companions of the Prophet","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 18, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Sa\u2019id al-Khudri reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cDo not insult my companions. If one of you were to spend the likes of mount Uhud in gold, it would not reach a small portion of theirs or even half of that.\" Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 3673,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":7912,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/10\/10\/disciple-zubair-awwam\/","url_meta":{"origin":19386,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Disciples: The Prophet&#8217;s disciple is Zubayr ibn &#8216;Awwam","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 10, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Jabir reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \"Verily, every prophet has a disciple, and my disciple is Al-Zubayr ibn al-'Awwam.\" Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 3719 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Bukhari \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u062c\u064e\u0627\u0628\u0650\u0631\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0651\u064f \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0625\u0650\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0644\u0650\u0643\u064f\u0644\u0651\u0650 \u0646\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0651\u064d \u062d\u064e\u0648\u064e\u0627\u0631\u0650\u064a\u0651\u064b\u0627 \u0648\u064e\u0625\u0650\u0646\u0651\u064e \u062d\u064e\u0648\u064e\u0627\u0631\u0650\u064a\u0651\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0632\u0651\u064f\u0628\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":6217,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/11\/most-beloved-sahabah-prophet\/","url_meta":{"origin":19386,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Sahaba: Most beloved companions to the Prophet","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 11, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"'Amr ibn al-'As reported: I said, \u201cWhich person is most beloved to you?\u201d The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cAisha.\u201d I said, \u201cI mean among men.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cHer father.\u201d I said, \u201cThen who?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cUmar ibn al-Khattab,\u201d and the Prophet mentioned other men.\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":285,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2010\/12\/24\/patience-prophet-companions-famine\/","url_meta":{"origin":19386,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Famine: Patience of the Prophet, companions with famine","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 24, 2010","format":false,"excerpt":"'Utbah ibn Ghazwan reported: I found myself as the seventh among seven who had been with the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him. We had nothing to eat but the leaves of a wild tree until the corners of our mouths were wounded. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2967\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/19386","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=19386"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp